Announcing version 0.5 of PyDitz, a drop-in replacement for Ditz, a
distributed bug tracker (http://ditz.rubyforge.org).

Changes in this version:

* bugfix: Issue names not replaced in comment text
* bugfix: Reconfigure clobbers existing file
* Add sortable tables to HTML output
* Write some user documentation
* Add a user config file

You can get PyDitz from:

  https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pyditz

or browse the sources at:

  https://bitbucket.org/zondo/pyditz

It's distributed under the GPL v2+.
